sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K123009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This Construct will allow for the detection and degredation of BPA in cells already containing the ER (K123003) biobrick. It works in two systems first. Together K123003 and K123009 produce a NOT gate where when Bisphenol A (BPA), Estrogen or any other estrogen mimic is in the system the product of K123003 dimerizes and attaches to the ERE site of K123009. This stops the production of TetR (R0040) by phsically stoping the Polymerase from transcribing it. This allows the pTet(C0040)promoter to turn on the production of RFP (E1010) for detection as well as BisdA(K123000) and BisdB(K123001)which allow for the degredation of BPA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jason Gardiner
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: While BisdA and BisdB have only been shown to degrade BPA we have put in RFP to allow for the detection of other estrogen mimics as well.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K123008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part when used will allow the production of TetR to increase the production of BisdA and BisdB. When produced BisdA and BisdB will cause the degredation of Bisphenol A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jason Gardiner

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BisdA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
When used in conjunction with BisdB this enzyme can be used to degrade Bisphenol A. Activity has previously been recorded in E.coli by Miho Sasaki1 et al. 2005.
Miho Sasaki1, Jun-ichi Maki, Ko-ichi Oshiman, Yoshinobu Matsumura1, and Tetsuaki Tsuchido.2005, Biodegradation of bisphenol A by cells and cell lysate from Sphingomonas sp. strain AO1. Biodegredation 16: 449-459
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jason Gardiner
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: These parts where designed to include a his tag to make it easier to view enzyme presence

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K123002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part contains LacIQ (BBa_I14032) and Estrogen Receptor Element (ERE) and TetR (BBa_C0040). The Estrogen Responsive element is to be used in conjunction with ER (Estrogen Receptor). This design involves ER binding to the ERE and disrupting the constituative promoter LacIQ from producing TetR via physically getting in the way of the polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jason Gardiner
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Estrogen Responsive Element was taken from the Human Estrogen Responsive Element
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There is some data that suggests the ER is toxic to the cell. However in our experiments while we did see a decrease in growth rate we did not find ER to be fatal to the cell.
